/// data : [{"id":12,"published_date":null,"location":"Itahari","title":"Campaign intber 2 nepal and uae","description":"<p>&nbsp;osdjfjdiskfja sdifj ldjslf&nbsp; hesfiuhsriufgn iuser fgiuhai fguhsdiufghaieworug flad iuf gaeriufg kruegfi ugsreiuf girsejbvi urwfhuaiwegrfuoiwheiou wdiouf gw4iug hfiuwd gf87w3iufg wdiou fgioure gfiuer ufiiuf vgfreio ug fvA meeting of a Joint Committee os taking place atday.nd Minister for Human Resources of the UAE, Dr Abdul Rahaman Abdul Manan Al Awar, would address the meeting in the inaugural session.ould lead the Nepali delegation in the meeting of technical group scheduled after the inaugural session.According to theview would be carried out on the implementation of the labour agreement signed between Nepal and the UAE in 2019.Discussion would be held on various issues including social securityeir safety in the workplace, arrangement of health service and insurance, skill development and increase in salary in the joint meeting.Similarly, the meeting would also held discussion to resolve problems of those Nepalis, who are in the UAE ind stranded there.Likewise, Minister Shrestha and Minister of the UAE, Dr Awar, are holding meeting today itself and discussion would be held on various issues related to safety and welfare of the Nepali workers.On the occasion, Minister Shrestha would discuss with his counterpart about the tourist visa and measures to resolve the problems created due to this, according to the Minister Shrestha&#39;s Secretariat.A Nepali delegation under the leadership of Minister Shrestha had left for the UAE on Monday. Nepali Ambassador to the UAE, Krishna Prasad Dhakal, welcomed the Nepali delegation at Abu Dhabi Airport.Minister Shrestha is scheduled to hold discussion with Nepali community regarding the problems facing by Nepali workers and measures to resolve it at the Nepali Embassy on Wednesday.</p>","type":1,"type_name":"News","file":"/notice/12/Test docx.docx"},{"id":11,"published_date":null,"location":"Duhabi","title":"Nepal ministry of campaign news","description":"<p>ahjflhsdfkds sdjfjahjklfhsd sjdhfjhsaA meeting of a would lead the Nepali delegation in the meeting of technical group scheduled after the inaugural session.According to iew would be carried out on the implementation of the labour agreement signed between Nepal and the UAE in 2019.iscussion would be held on various issues including social security o, their safety in the workplace, arrangement of health service and insurance, skill development and increase in salary in the joint meeting.Similarly, the meeting would also held discussion to resolve problems of those Nepalis, who are in the UAEnd stranded there.Likewise, Minister Shrestha and Minister of the UAE, Dr Awar, are holding meeting today itself and discussion would be held on various issues related to safety and welfare of the Nepali workers.On the occasion, Minister Shrestha would discuss with his counterpart about the tourist visa and measures to resolve the problems created due to this, according to the Minister Shrestha&#39;s Secretariat.A Nepali delegation under the leadership of Minister Shrestha had left for the UAE on Monday. Nepali Ambassador to the UAE, Krishna Prasad Dhakal, welcomed the Nepali delegation at Abu Dhabi Airport.Minister Shrestha is scheduled to hold discussion with Nepali community regarding the problems facing by Nepali workers and measures to resolve it at the Nepali Embassy on Wednesday.</p>","type":1,"type_name":"News","file":"/notice/11/Test docx.docx"},{"id":10,"published_date":null,"location":"Itahari","title":"Nepal-UAE Joint Committee meeting: Nepal stressing on social security, safety of Nepali workers","description":"<p>A meeting of a Joint Committee of<a href=\"https://nepalnews.com.np/s/sports/saaf-u-18-women-s-championship-commences\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;Nepal</a>&nbsp;and the<a href=\"https://nepalnews.com.np/s/nation/labor-minister-shrestha-going-to-uae\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;United Arab Emirates</a>&nbsp;is taking place at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nepalnews.com.np/s/nation/labor-minister-shrestha-going-to-uae\" target=\"_blank\">Abu Dhabi&nbsp;</a>today.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://nepalnews.com.np/s/nation/labor-minister-shrestha-going-to-uae\" target=\"_blank\">Minister for Labour, Employment and Social Security, Krishna Kumar Shrestha</a>, and Minister for Human Resources of the UAE, Dr Abdul Rahaman Abdul Manan Al Awar, would address the meeting in the inaugural session.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://nepalnews.com.np/s/nation/nepal-uk-agree-to-establish-labour-relation\" target=\"_blank\">Joint-Secretary of the Labour Ministry, Rajeev Pokharel</a>, would lead the Nepali delegation in the meeting of technical group scheduled after the inaugural session.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nepalnews.com.np/s/capital/labour-ministry-gets-permission-to-construct-labour-hospital\" target=\"_blank\">Labour Ministry</a>, a review would be carried out on the implementation of the labour agreement signed between Nepal and the UAE in 2019.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Discussion would be held on various issues including social security of<a href=\"https://nepalnews.com.np/s/nation/saudi-prince-in-the-capital-bilateral-talks-tomorrow\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;Nepali workers in UAE</a>, their safety in the workplace, arrangement of health service and insurance, skill development and increase in salary in the joint meeting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Similarly, the meeting would also held discussion to resolve problems of those Nepalis, who are in the UAE in<a href=\"https://nepalnews.com.np/s/travel-and-tourism/egypt-s-ancient-finds-to-pull-tourism-out-of-pandemic\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;tourist visa&nbsp;</a>and stranded there.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Likewise, Minister Shrestha and Minister of the UAE, Dr Awar, are holding meeting today itself and discussion would be held on various issues related to safety and welfare of the Nepali workers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On the occasion, Minister Shrestha would discuss with his counterpart about the tourist visa and measures to resolve the problems created due to this, according to the Minister Shrestha&#39;s Secretariat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A Nepali delegation under the leadership of Minister Shrestha had left for the UAE on Monday. Nepali Ambassador to the UAE, Krishna Prasad Dhakal, welcomed the Nepali delegation at Abu Dhabi Airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Minister Shrestha is scheduled to hold discussion with Nepali community regarding the problems facing by Nepali workers and measures to resolve it at the Nepali Embassy on Wednesday.</p>","type":0,"type_name":"Notice","file":"/notice/10/Test docx.docx"},{"id":9,"published_date":null,"location":"Itahari","title":"Labour ministry gets permission to construct labour hospital","description":"<p>The government has given permission in principle for the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nepalnews.com.np/s/capital/minister-ale-visits-pashupati-premises\" target=\"_blank\">construction</a>&nbsp;of a labour hospital. The cabinet meeting held on Thursday gave permission for it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://nepalnews.com.np/s/nation/systematic-reforms-necessary-for-more-remittance-labour-minister\" target=\"_blank\">Minister for Labour</a>, Employment and Social Security, Krishna Kumar Shrestha, had under the coordination of Joint-Secretary Shesh Narayan Poudel to carry out a feasibility study for the construction of the hospital meant for workers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to Minister Shrestha&#39;s Secretariat, the team has been carrying out a study on human, material, financial and managerial resources, operation modalities as well as other aspects for the operation of the hospital.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Minister Shrestha had presented the proposal putting the construction of labour hospital in priority in order to make arrangements of treatment services to workers contributing to the country&#39;s development at affordable prices as there is already separate hospital for Nepali Army, Nepal Police,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nepalnews.com.np/s/sports/deumai-gold-cup-football-to-begin-feb-19-in-ilam\" target=\"_blank\">Armed Police Force</a>&nbsp;and civil servants in the country.</p>","type":0,"type_name":"Notice","file":"/notice/9/Test docx.docx"},{"id":8,"published_date":null,"location":"Biratnagar","title":"Local levels’ plans should incorporate people’s needs: Labor Minister Shrestha","description":"<p>Minister for Labour, Employment and Social Security,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nepalnews.com.np/s/issues/concerns-on-welfare-of-nepali-workers-discussed-in-abu-dhabi-dialogue\" target=\"_blank\">Krishna Kumar Shrestha</a>, has stressed that local level plans should reflect the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nepalnews.com.np/s/global/why-bidens-immigration-plan-may-be-risky-for-democrats\" target=\"_blank\">needs of people</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In his address to an annual review meeting organized today by the Tanahu District Coordination Committee at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nepalnews.com.np/s/nation/good-neighbours-provides-relief-materials-to-disaster-victims-in-bandipur\" target=\"_blank\">Bandipur Rural Municipality</a>-5, the Minister was of the view that locals&rsquo; needs should be the baseline of plans of local governments.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Highlighting the need for common understanding and collaboration among all political parties for development endeavors, he called for collective efforts to build Tanahu prosperous. &ldquo;<a href=\"https://nepalnews.com.np/s/nation/pm-deuba-urges-environment-friendly-development\" target=\"_blank\">Development activities</a>&nbsp;should not be politicised.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://nepalnews.com.np/s/global/voting-for-japan-s-general-election-starts-as-pm-kishida-seeks-mandate\" target=\"_blank\">House of Representatives&nbsp;</a>(HoR) member Kalila Khan, NA member Prakash Path and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nepalnews.com.np/s/travel-and-tourism/gandaki-govt-committed-to-developing-bandipur-gandaki-cm-pokharel\" target=\"_blank\">Gandaki Province</a>&nbsp;Assembly member Ram Bahadur Gurung among others stressed the need for&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nepalnews.com.np/s/nation/media-expert-regmee-highlights-need-of-health-safety-guideline-for-journalists\" target=\"_blank\">media roles&nbsp;</a>to promote the good efforts of local governments.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Administrative officers from different local levels in the districts: Byas, Shuklagandaki, Bhimad, and Bhanu municipalities and Ghiring, Devghat, Bandipur, Aabukhaireni, Rhishing, and Myagde rural municipalities represented the annual progress reports of the respective offices.&nbsp;</p>","type":0,"type_name":"Notice","file":"/notice/8/Test docx.docx"},{"id":7,"published_date":null,"location":"Biratnagar","title":"युकेएड सीप र रोजगारी सर्भिसेस द्वारा “अब देशमै छ रोजगारी\" अभियान आधिकारिक रूपमा सुरूवात !","description":"<p>३० जुलाईमा आयोजित एक भर्चुअल कार्यक्रममा माननीय अर्थमन्त्री&nbsp;डा. युवराज खतिवडा ले आधिकारिक रूपमा &quot;अब देशमै छ रोजगारी&quot; अभियान प्रवर्तन गर्नुभयो। सो कार्यक्रममा प्रमुख उद्योगपतिहरू, स्किलिङ इकोसिस्टम सरोकारवाला, दाताहरु, मिडिया तथा&nbsp;नागरिक समाज प्रतिनिधिहरूको सहभागिता रहेको थियो। रोजगारी सर्भिस र युकेएड स्किल फर इम्प्लोइमेन्ट प्रोग्राम (सीप) को पहलमा यो अभियान प्रवासी पुनरागमनहरु र अन्य आर्थिक रुपले वञ्चित, समाजिक बहिष्कृत समूहहरुको जीवनयापन आवश्यकताहरुको प्रतिकृया दिन यो अभियान थालिएको हो ।&nbsp;युकेएड सीप र रोजगारी सर्भिसले रोजगार अवसर, उद्यमशीलता बढाउन र माइग्रेसनको अनुकूलन गरी उद्योग र आर्थिक बृद्धि गर्नका लागि काम गरिरहेको छ। यस अभियान मार्फत युकेएड सीप र रोजगारी सर्भिसले विभिन्न सरोकारवालासँगको साझेदारीले नेपालको मानव संसाधनमार्फत रोजगार, उद्योग र वृद्धि गर्न सहयोग पुर्याउने छ।</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>अभियानको लोगो र नारा सार्वजनिक गर्दै मन्त्री खतिवडाले भने, &lsquo;म विश्वस्त छु कि यस्ता बजार नेतृत्वका पहलहरुले गति लिन पाउँनेछन र सफलतापूर्वक सरकार, निजी क्षेत्र, नागरिक समाज, स्किलिंग पार्टनर, मिडिया र हाम्रा विकास पार्टनरबीच परिकल्पना गरिएको सहकार्य निमार्ण गर्नेछ ।&rsquo; उनले रोजगारी सृजना र उद्यमशील वर्गको निर्माण महत्वपूर्ण भएको र सरकारले स्मार्ट प्रोत्साहन र बजारमैत्री नीतिहरु ल्याइरहेको उनले बताए।</p>\r\n\r\n<p>कोभिड&mdash;१९ ले गर्दा अर्को वर्ष मात्र लगभग ७ लाख नेपाली&nbsp;वैदेशिक कामदारहरुले रोजगारी गुमाएर स्वदेश फर्किने अनुमान गरिएको छ। यसले निम्त्याउने&nbsp;बेरोजगारीको संकटबाट बच्नका लागि नेपालले १० लाख भन्दा बढि रोजगारी सृजना गर्नु आवश्यक छ। &quot;यदि समयमै यो संकटलाई जवाफ दिन हामी&nbsp;सक्षम भएनौ भने यसले&nbsp;सबै क्षेत्रमा प्रतिकुल लहर झल्काउन सक्छ र हालका दशकमा मिहिनेतले हासिल गरेको प्रगतिलाई उल्ट्याउन सक्छ, यो समयमा हाम्रो लक्ष्य भनेको यो सुनिश्चित गर्नु हो कि हामी नेपालको मानवीय&nbsp;पूंजी&nbsp;उठाउन सथै नेपालीहरुको जीवन र आजीविकाको रक्षा गर्न हामी सक्षम छौं। &quot; युकेएड सीपका टिम लिडर बलजीत बोहोराले बताउनुभयो।</p>","type":0,"type_name":"Notice","file":"/notice/7/Test docx.docx"},{"id":6,"published_date":null,"location":"Duhabi","title":"कार्पेन्टरको तालिम संचालन","description":"<p><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41);\">दक्ष सीपयुक्त जनशक्तिको उत्पादन गर्ने उदेश्यले रोजगारी सर्भिसेस द्वारा प्रदेश ५, नेपालगंजमा १५ जना स्थानीयको सक्रिय सहभागीमा कार्पेन्टरको तालिम सम्पन्न भएकाे छ।</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" height=\"233\" src=\"/medias/index_2022_04_26_09_25_26.jpeg\" width=\"175\" /></p>","type":0,"type_name":"Notice","file":"/notice/6/Test docx.docx"},{"id":5,"published_date":null,"location":"Itahari","title":"एच.आर. ह्यापपि हावर 2020 नेपालगंजमा सम्पन्न","description":"<p>रोजगारी सर्भिसेस प्रा. लि. द्वारा सीप तथा युके एडको सहकार्यमा फागुन ०७, २०७६ मङ्गलवारका दिन नेपालगंज स्थित सिग्नेट होटलमा HR Happy Hour 2020 आयोजना गरेको छ​।</p>\r\n\r\n<p>प्रदेश नम्बर -५ का उधोग वाणिज्य संघ लगायत ब्यपारिक वर्गहरुको सहभागीतामा भएको कार्यक्रममा रोजगारी सर्भिसेस प्रा. लि. का प्रबन्ध निर्देशक श्री शैलेन्द्र राज गिरीले उधोगिहरुलाई कम्पनीमा मानव संसाधनको ब्यबस्थापन कसरी गर्ने लगायतका प्रक्रियागत बिधिहरुको बारेमा जानकारी गराउनु भ​एको थियो।</p>\r\n\r\n<p>कार्यक्रममा उधोगिहरुलाई कम्पनीमा मानव संसाधनको ब्यबस्थापन कसरी गर्ने लगायतका प्रक्रियागत बिधिहरुको बारेमा जानकारी गराईनु का साथै मानव संसाधन सम्बन्धि विभिन्न विभिन्न विषयहरुमा अन्तरक्रिया भएको थियो।</p>\r\n\r\n<p>उधोगहरुमा मानव संसाधनको ब्यबस्थापन र व्यव्स्थित गर्ने उदेश्यले संचालित सो कार्यक्रम रोजगारी सर्भिस प्राईभेट लिमिटेडका प्रबन्ध निर्देशक श्री शैलेन्द्रराज गिरीले मोडरेट गरेका थिए । &quot;हामी आशा गर्दछौं यस कार्यक्रममा भ​एका छलफलहरु सबैका लागि उपयोगी र उपलब्धि मुलुक&nbsp;रह्यो,&quot; रोजगारी सर्भिस प्रा. लि. का प्रा. लि. का बिजनेस डाईरेक्टर संजीव कुमार निरौलाले बताउनु भयो।</p>\r\n\r\n<p>रोजगारी सर्भिस प्रा. लि. का सीप कार्यक्रम अन्तर्गत रोजगारी पसलका प्रोजेक्ट म्यानेजर मनोज सुनुवारले ,&nbsp;विश्व बजार लगायत नेपाली उधोगिहरुको स्थिति र सफलताका साकारात्मक संदेशको बारेमा समेत&nbsp;कार्यक्रममा छलफल भएको जानकारी दिनुभयो।</p>","type":0,"type_name":"Notice","file":"/notice/5/Test docx.docx"},{"id":4,"published_date":null,"location":"Biratnagar","title":"अब देशमै छ रोजगारी Campaign Launch Live","description":"<p><span style=\"color: rgb(28, 30, 33);\">अब देशमै छ रोजगारी Campaign Launch</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/SkillsforEmploymentProgrammeNepal/videos/345375186858482/UzpfSTM1NzQ0MzUzMDk3MzMyNzozNDY3OTgyNDM5OTE5NDA1/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color: rgb(28, 30, 33);\" target=\"_blank\">Watch Live</a><img alt=\"\" height=\"200\" src=\"/medias/news4_2022_04_26_09_33_45.png\" width=\"347\" /></p>","type":1,"type_name":"News","file":"/notice/4/Test docx.docx"},{"id":3,"published_date":null,"location":"Duhabi","title":"वैदेशिक रोजगारीबाट फर्किएर स्वदेशमा उद्यम गरी बसेका उद्यमीलाई राष्ट्रिय सम्मान तथा पुरस्कारको लागि आवेदन दिने सम्बन्धी सूचना","description":"<p><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41);\">काठमाडौं, १० जेनेवरी २०२०, नेपालको मानव संसाधन क्षेत्रको इतिहासमा, नेपालमै पहिलोपल्ट, मानव संशाधनको आवश्यकता बारे जनचेतना जगाउने उदेश्यले, उद्योगी, ब्यापारी, मानव संसाधन विज्ञ तथा अभ्यासकर्ता, संस्थाका प्रमुखहरुलाइ लक्षित गरि रियल सल्युसंस, मेरोजब, रोजगारी सर्भिसेस तथा आयुलोजीकको संयुक्त आयोजनामा काठमाडौं स्थित हायात होटलमा एच आर फेस्टिभल समारोह आयोजना भएको छ।</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(29, 33, 41);\">﻿</span></p>","type":1,"type_name":"News","file":null}]
